5:
World Flipper, activated. Prepare for
launch.
9:
Damn it all to hell! How many times
has this thing sent us back now?!
18:
I understand your fervent desire to
reach the Overlords without delay...
But I fear that we might be rushing
headlong into this without thinking.
23:
What about that guy you met in the
abyss? Nova, was it? Ain't he
supposed to be coming back?
26:
If he is, we don't need to go all
gung-ho like this. We can just wait
here—if the big robots come, we'll
take 'em out just like before.
31: But, all of this is my—
42:
Oh my! I gotta say, I wasn't
expecting this warm a
welcome—you guys are gonna
make me blush here!
46:
You sure about that, Lelucia? They
look just about ready to tear us to
pieces!
50:
Long time no see, you two.
And sorry, we've been on edge
lately, due to... well, just about
everything.
55:
Well I'll be! So you were actually a
goddess all along, Stella?
59:
I am a tool—as is Starview Village
itself. We were put here to impede
all travel between worlds.
62:
The ones who created me—the
Overlords—forbade anyone from
using the World Flipper, or any
power similar to it.
64:
My role was to observe and
suppress. If the situation demanded
it, I would also bring down
punishment... in the form of a purge.
72:
She definitely knew about all of this.
That's why she was so careful to put
her world on complete lockdown.
78:
Any chance I could get a free pass
on this no inter-world travel rule? I
don't think I could financially recover
from a blow like that! Throw me a
bone here, Stella!
84:
Lelucia! There's a time and a place
for business talk—and it is NOT now!
Have a little more tact!
87:
Hey, I'm just trying to be pragmatic
and forward-thinking here! A
situation this grim calls for a bit of
optimism, don't you think?
91:
It's the Overlords you need to be
asking, not Stella. They're also not
the negotiating type, so, good luck
with that.
96:
Indeed... The "Purgers," as you called
them... They are but footsoldiers of
the Overlords, and they cannot be
reasoned with. They only know
indiscriminate destruction.
99:
Perhaps this realization comes too
late, but... I think I finally understand
how the fiends felt about me.
103:
But... why are they so intent on doing
this?
106:
What's so bad about traveling to
another world?
110: Their true intentions are a mystery.
113:
But I do know that the events which
occurred on Light's world were
precisely what they feared most.
119:
Worlds which have begun to fuse
together amass greater weight, and
eventually begin to draw in other
worlds. This starts a chain reaction.
121:
Then, when they can no longer bear
the weight, the worlds begin to
collapse. In their midst, a tear forms.
123:
That is the abyss. It is a realm where
even the laws of reality—of life and
death—are different. It is a
singularity, linked to distant worlds.
129:
Wait, does that mean the
Kaleidoscope... is connected to the
abyss?!
132:
Yes. The link is likely to have
emerged synchronously with the
changes that happened on Light's
world.
136:
The events that transpired on my
world happened 50 years ago...
Which is precisely how long the
Kaleidoscope has existed.
140:
A s-singularity? Collapsing worlds?!
Sounds like we have WAY bigger
problems than Lelucia going
bankrupt!
145:
That is all I can piece together from
the memories I regained. I'm sorry I
can't do more.
148:
My remaining memories...
She must still have them.
153:
That's why we've made up our
minds to go and see the
Overlords.
We won't stay in the dark
anymore—we need to know
everything.
157:
Doesn't matter if we want to go for
tea with them or kick their
asses—we still have no idea how to
even GET to these Overlord bastards.
162:
I see...
In that case, I wonder if I could ask
you to come with me for a moment.
169:
Huh? Isn't this just the usual route we
take when going to Palpebra?
172: That it is! A familiar sight, isn't it?
174:
But I bet you didn't know that this is
actually a holy place for us
Sheephirds!
185:
Oh come on, Lilie! How did YOU not
know that? You need to take more
of an interest in your own people's
past!
189:
What can I say—history was never
my best subject!
194:
Well everyone, get ready, 'cause I'll
be guiding you to where the
Sheephirds reside! There's
something I want to check out there,
you see...
197:
Who knows—maybe some of my
ancestors were actually old friends
of yours, Stella!
